Is it really that hard to understand what's different about this game? If it were just a matter of cracking some routine security scheme, it woulda been done day 1 with the hacking talent paying attention to this game. The issue is SERVER-SIDE CONTENT. There's no way for the game to run, legit or not without downloading a pile of content every time you use it. No high-speed internet, no game. Eventually, the content will probably be intercepted, catalogued, and released as a version-locked standalone. Which will make the pirated Diablo 3 actually more valuable because you it won't require always on internet. Sure it won't have "updates" and "surprises" that Blizzard drops, but I've had enough of Blizzard's "surprises" right now anyway.
